      AB

      Use the Games Played slider to exclude players outside the specified Games Played range. For MLB, this slider filters players by At Bats.

      Slates

      Use the salary slider to exclude players outside the specified salary range.

      FPTS

      Use the fantasy points slider to exclude players outside the specified fantasy point range. Note that this could refer to average fantasy points per game or the RotoGrinders projections depending the page.

      PT/$

      Use the value slider to exlude players outside the specified value range. Player value is defined as (fpts / (salary / 1000)). A high point per dollar ratio indicates strong value, whereas a low point per dollar ratio indicates weak value.

        NFL Projections are first updated by Tuesday at 11 AM EST for the upcoming week. Football Outsiders stats are updated by Tuesday at 10 PM EST. NBA/MLB Projections are updated daily at 11 AM EST for that day's games. Projections are updated as news breaks throughout the day/week.

        *Stats such as SIERA, xFIP, and HR/FB rely on subjective judgement calls of fly balls vs. line drives and therefore may not match analytic sites using different providers.

        • P - Probable
        • O - Out
        • Q - Questionable
        • GTD - Game-Time Decision
        • D - Doubtful (NFL/NBA), Disabled (MLB)
        • IFO - Game-Time Decision. If Player is Out, use Back-up Player for Good Value
        • CS - Check Status. A potential sleeper whose value relies on the status of the player above him on the depth chart. Check the status of the star player to determine if this sleeper has value.
